        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-16T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-16T06:00:00-05:00" n="955" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d955">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6363/5–1649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-16T19:00:00+08:00">May 16, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 16—7:34 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1667. Fuel supply situation Shanghai Power Company critical with sudden stoppage
                    of shipping. Oil and coal stocks on hand will last 10 to 15 days. Present load
                    factor 91,000 KW or 54 per cent capacity and 37 per cent below demand same
                    period 1948. Reputed Caltex supply 40,000 ton fuel oil. If made available to
                    SPC, power supply maintainable 65 days at present load demand but once Shanghai
                    occupied, ECA financing ceases and Caltex will require payment foreign exchange
                    with sources, facilities, procedures not now visible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
